        "description": "Currently, if you send an INT and TERM signal to a parent plasma store process (Python one) it terminates it without cleaning the child process. This makes it hard to run plasma store in non-interactive mode. Inside shell ctrl-c kills both processes.\r\n\r\nMoreover, INT prints out an ugly KeyboardInterrup exception. Probably something nicer should be done.",
